    "id": 30,
    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks — April 30, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-30",
    "tags": ["GPT-5.5", "Biosecurity", "OpenAI-Microsoft", "Anthropic", "AWS Trainium"],
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 30, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 GPT-5.5 showed up as OpenAI's new work model and immediately started flexing benchmarks\n\nThe frontier labs have fully abandoned modesty. We now launch models the way chip companies launch aircraft carriers.\n\n- **The rollout:** OpenAI released GPT-5.5 on April 23, 2026 to ChatGPT and Codex, with GPT-5.5 Pro rolling out in ChatGPT and API availability promised soon after additional safety work.\n- **The benchmark pitch:** OpenAI says GPT-5.5 hit 82.7% on Terminal-Bench 2.0, 58.6% on SWE-Bench Pro, 78.7% on OSWorld-Verified, and 84.4% on BrowseComp, while keeping GPT-5.4-class serving latency and using fewer tokens on Codex tasks.\n\n*The new baseline for an AI launch is apparently: do real work, use tools, and bring a spreadsheet of receipts.*\n\n**Sources:** [Introducing GPT-5.5](https://openai.com/index/introducing-gpt-5-5/) | [GPT-5.5 System Card](https://deploymentsafety.openai.com/gpt-5-5/internal-research-debugging-evaluation)\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 OpenAI also opened a GPT-5.5 bio jailbreak contest because normal bug bounties were too ordinary\n\nShipping the model and then paying researchers to break its bio safeguards is at least a refreshingly direct form of confidence.\n\n- **What is in scope:** OpenAI's GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty, announced April 23, 2026, asks vetted researchers to find one universal jailbreak that clears all five bio safety questions in a clean chat on GPT-5.5 in Codex Desktop.\n- **What is on the line:** the first true universal jailbreak pays $25,000, applications stay open until June 22, 2026, and testing runs from April 28 to July 27 under NDA.\n\n*AI safety now comes with prize money, application windows, and a slightly unnerving amount of specificity.*\n\n**Sources:** [GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty](https://openai.com/index/gpt-5-5-bio-bug-bounty/) | [GPT-5.5 System Card](https://deploymentsafety.openai.com/gpt-5-5/trust-based-access)\n\n---\n\n## 🤝 OpenAI and Microsoft rewired their partnership without actually breaking up\n\nThe relationship has reached that very modern stage where both sides want more flexibility and still need each other's datacenters.\n\n- **What changed:** On April 27, 2026, OpenAI said Microsoft remains its primary cloud partner and still gets first launch on Azure unless it cannot support the needed capabilities, while OpenAI can now serve products across any cloud provider.\n- **The commercial reset:** Microsoft's license to OpenAI IP now runs through 2032 on a non-exclusive basis, Microsoft no longer pays revenue share to OpenAI, and OpenAI's own revenue-share payments to Microsoft continue through 2030 with a cap.\n\n*When the AI stack gets big enough, even the alliances start needing their own governance layer.*\n\n**Sources:** [The next phase of the Microsoft OpenAI partnership](https://openai.com/index/next-phase-of-microsoft-partnership/) | [OpenAI company updates](https://openai.com/)\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Anthropic and Amazon turned their cloud relationship into a gigawatt-scale power deal\n\nWe have moved well beyond \"startup signs cloud contract\" and into \"frontier lab secures its own chunk of industrial civilization.\"\n\n- **The new agreement:** Anthropic announced on April 20, 2026 that it had signed a new deal with Amazon securing up to 5 gigawatts of compute capacity to train and deploy Claude, including Trainium2 capacity coming online in the first half of 2026 and nearly 1 GW of Trainium2 and Trainium3 by year-end.\n- **The money and infrastructure:** Anthropic said it will commit more than $100 billion over ten years to AWS technologies, currently uses over one million Trainium2 chips, and that Amazon is investing $5 billion now with up to $20 billion more in the future.\n\n*The AI race increasingly looks like power procurement wearing an API badge.*\n\n**Sources:** [Anthropic and Amazon expand collaboration for up to 5 gigawatts of new compute](https://www.anthropic.com/news/anthropic-amazon-compute) | [Anthropic newsroom](https://www.anthropic.com/news)\n"
  }
]
